<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="content-block legal">
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: June 2026</p>

      <p>The Guelph-Humber Pre-Law Society ("we", "us", "the Society") is a student club at the University of Guelph-Humber. This policy explains what personal information we collect through this website and how we use it. We follow the principles of Canada's <em>Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act</em> (PIPEDA).</p>

      <h3>1. Information we collect</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contact form:</strong> when you message us, we collect the name, email address, and message you submit. These are sent to us through Netlify Forms.</li>
        <li><strong>Photos:</strong> we publish event and competition photos that may show identifiable people. We only post photos taken at Society events or shared with us for that purpose.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> use advertising trackers, and we do not sell or rent personal information to anyone.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>2. How we use it</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>To respond to your inquiries and follow up about membership, competitions, or events.</li>
        <li>To promote the Society and its activities (e.g. publishing event photos).</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>3. Where it is stored</h3>
      <p>This site is hosted by Netlify, and contact-form submissions are processed by Netlify's form service. Their handling of data is governed by Netlify's own privacy policy. Photos and page content are stored in our website's code repository on GitHub.</p>

      <h3>4. Photo removal &amp; your rights</h3>
      <p>You have the right to ask what personal information we hold about you, to correct it, or to have it removed. <strong>If you appear in a photo and want it taken down, contact us and we will remove it promptly.</strong> Requests can be made through our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> or by messaging us on <a href="{{ site.instagram }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram</a>.</p>

      <h3>5. Children &amp; students</h3>
      <p>This site is aimed at university students and the general public. We do not knowingly collect information from anyone under 13.</p>

      <h3>6. Changes to this policy</h3>
      <p>We may update this policy from time to time. The "last updated" date above will always reflect the current version.</p>

      <h3>7. Contact</h3>
      <p>Questions about this policy or your information? Reach us through the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> or on <a href="{{ site.instagram }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram</a>{% if site.email %}, or by email at <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>{% endif %}.</p>

      <p class="legal-disclaimer"><strong>Note:</strong> This Society is a student organization and is not the University of Guelph-Humber itself. This policy is provided in good faith and is not legal advice.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
